<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><TimeML><TIMEX3 tid="t0" functionInDocument="CREATION_TIME"/>Reporters and technical employees at the BBC were  <EVENT eid="e1" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">holding</EVENT> a <TIMEX3 tid="t1" type="DURATION">24-hour</TIMEX3> <EVENT eid="e2" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">strike</EVENT> <TIMEX3 tid="t2" type="DATE">Tuesday</TIMEX3> to <EVENT eid="e3" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="INFINITIVE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">protest</EVENT> plans that would <EVENT eid="e4" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="would">link</EVENT> salary to  performance.&#13;
Radio programs were at a minimum and the BBC television station was <EVENT eid="e5" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PAST" aspect="PROGRESSIVE" polarity="POS" modality="none">runnig</EVENT>  movies <TIMEX3 tid="t3" type="TIME">Tuesday morning</TIMEX3> instead of its usual programming.&#13;
The <EVENT eid="e6" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">strike</EVENT> was <EVENT eid="e7" class="I_ACTION" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">called</EVENT> by the National Union of Journalists (NUJ) which is  opposed to plans <EVENT eid="e8" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PRESPART" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">linking</EVENT> salary to employee performance in order to <EVENT eid="e9" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="INFINITIVE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">save</EVENT> the  company 50 million pounds (75 million dollars) <TIMEX3 tid="t4" type="DATE">this year</TIMEX3>.&#13;
The union <EVENT eid="e10" class="REPORTING" tense="PRESENT" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">says</EVENT> that the <EVENT eid="e11" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">proposal</EVENT> means employees would be <EVENT eid="e12" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="would">overworked</EVENT>.&#13;
The BBC management, meanwhile, has <EVENT eid="e13" class="REPORTING" tense="PRESENT" aspect="PERFECTIVE" polarity="POS" modality="none">told</EVENT> employees that they would not be  <EVENT eid="e14" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="NEG" modality="would">paid</EVENT> for the <EVENT eid="e15" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">strike</EVENT> day and <EVENT eid="e16" class="I_ACTION" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">denied</EVENT> that it has <EVENT eid="e17" class="I_ACTION" tense="PRESENT" aspect="PERFECTIVE" polarity="POS" modality="none">threatened</EVENT> to <EVENT eid="e18" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="INFINITIVE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">fire</EVENT> those who  <EVENT eid="e19" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">walked</EVENT> off the job <TIMEX3 tid="t5" type="DATE">Tuesday</TIMEX3> or <EVENT eid="e20" class="I_ACTION" tense="PRESENT" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">block</EVENT> their promotions.&#13;
The <EVENT eid="e21" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">strike</EVENT> was the first at the BBC since <TIMEX3 tid="t6" type="DATE">1989</TIMEX3>.&#13;
